article.headline: Gardner-Webb 67, Charleston Southern 62
article.story: BOILING SPRINGS, N.C. -- Kevin Hartley scored 21 points and Jerome Hill pulled down 10 rebounds to lead Gardner-Webb to a 67-62 victory over Charleston Southern in overtime on Wednesday night. Gardner-Webb's Tyler Strange made a 3-pointer to tie the game 57-57 with 43 seconds left in regulation. Hartley hit a 3-pointer for a 62-59 lead in the extra period, and the Bulldogs knocked down 7 of 8 free throws in overtime to claim the victory. Tashan Newsome scored 14 points and Strange 11 for the Bulldogs (19-11, 10-5 Big South Conference), who have won six straight. Saah Nimley had 15 points and Paul Gombwer 14 for the Buccaneers (16-11, 11-4), who lost to the Bulldogs 74-73 in overtime in January. Charleston Southern is tied with High Point, which lost to Radford 63-58, in the conference. Gardner-Webb made 11 of 28 3-pointers to Charleston Southern's 5 of 17.
